  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/smartphones/\" rel=\"tag\">智能手机</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"cn.engadget.com/2013/11/23/motorola-inks-deal-with-3d-systems-to-build-modular-ara-smartphones/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hss-prod.hss.aol.com/hss/storage/adam/5072f38bf00059d28d8a6af769db764f/ara1blogpost.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n早前 Motorola 宣布将会把 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/Phonebloks/\">Phonebloks</a> 这个模组型化手机概念成真，而且他们一直以来都有继续跟进的呢。Motorola 宣布他们已经跟 3D Systems 达成协议，後者将会为 Moto 生产「<a href=\"http://chinese.engadget.com/2013/10/29/motorola-project-ara-phonebloks/\">Project Ara</a>」手机，Moto 更尊称 3D Systems 为「未来工厂」呢。根据协议内容，3D Systems 将会为 Moto 创造「多物料打印技术，包括传导性物料和功能性物料」，用来制造 Ara 手机的模组，最终目标是将产量提升至应付得到消费者的需求。到底两公司何时才能真正实现大家自行升级手机的梦想呢？目前还没有时间表呢。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/11/22/motorola-inks-deal-with-3d-systems-to-build-modular-ara-smartphones/\">Engadget</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/23/motorola-inks-deal-with-3d-systems-to-build-modular-ara-smartphones/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20774673/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/23/motorola-inks-deal-with-3d-systems-to-build-modular-ara-smartphones/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
